Linux Training - Module 1:


5. Create 3 files in a dir1 and re-direct the output of list command with sorted by timestamp of the files to a file.
ANS:
afreen@Afreen:~$ mkdir dir1
afreen@Afreen:~$ cd dir1
afreen@Afreen:~/dir1$ touch file1 file2 file3
afreen@Afreen:~/dir1$ ls -lt > outputfile
afreen@Afreen:~/dir1$ cat outputfile
total 0
-rw-rw-r-- 1 afreen afreen 0 Jan 22 20:47 outputfile
-rw-rw-r-- 1 afreen afreen 0 Jan 22 20:43 file1
-rw-rw-r-- 1 afreen afreen 0 Jan 22 20:43 file2
-rw-rw-r-- 1 afreen afreen 0 Jan 22 20:43 file3

